The paper discusses visual question answering for videos, which involves understanding the temporal structure of the videos and the phrasal structures of the answers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, since the paper deals with video data, it may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
